人工智能新闻 https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/人工智能新闻2024 年 11 月 5 日，星期二 12:58:17 +0000 en-GB每小时1 https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/ai-icon-60x60.png人工智能新闻https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/ 32 32
西方司机仍然对车载人工智能持怀疑态度https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/news/western-drivers-remain-sceptical-in-vehicle-ai/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=western-drivers-remain-sceptical-in-vehicle-ai https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/news/western-drivers-remain-sceptical-in-vehicle-ai/#respondRyan Daws Tue, 05 Nov 2024 12:58:15 +0000 ApplicationsArtificial IntelligenceEthics & SocietyIndustriesResearchVirtual AssistantsVoice Recognitionaiartificial intelligenceautomotiveCarsconnected carsconnected vehiclesin-vehicle aimotoringreportstudyvehicles https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/?p=16437 <p>一项全球研究揭示了东西方市场对车载人工智能的态度形成鲜明对比，其中欧洲司机尤其不愿意。这项由 MHP 进行的研究调查了中国、美国、德国、英国、意大利、瑞典和波兰的 4,700 名汽车司机，揭示了人工智能接受和理解方面的显着地理差异。 <a class="excerpt-read-more" href="https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/news/western-drivers-remain-sceptical-in-vehicle-ai/" title="西方司机仍然对车载人工智能持怀疑态度">... 阅读更多 ”</a></p><p>后<a href="https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/news/western-drivers-remain-sceptical-in-vehicle-ai/">西方司机对车载人工智能仍持怀疑态度，</a>这首先出现在<a href="https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com">《人工智能新闻》</a>上。</p> ; 
<p>一项全球研究揭示了东西方市场对车载人工智能的态度形成鲜明对比，其中欧洲司机尤其不愿意。</p><p>这项由<a href="https://www.mhp.com/">MHP</a>进行的研究调查了中国、美国、德国、英国、意大利、瑞典和波兰的 4,700 名汽车司机，揭示了人工智能接受和理解方面的显着地理差异。</p><p>该研究表明，虽然人工智能正在成为现代汽车不可或缺的一部分，但欧洲消费者对其实施和价值主张仍然犹豫不决。</p><h3 class="wp-block-heading">地区差异</h3><p>研究发现，48% 的中国受访者主要将车载人工智能视为一个机会，而只有 23% 的欧洲受访者持这种乐观态度。在欧洲，39% 的人认为人工智能的机遇和风险大致平衡，而 24% 的人持消极立场，表明风险大于潜在收益。</p><p>对人工智能技术的理解也因地区而异。虽然超过 80% 的中国受访者声称了解人工智能在汽车中的应用，但欧洲驾驶员的这一数字下降至仅为 54%，凸显了明显的知识差距。</p><p> MHP 合伙人、该研究的作者之一 Marcus Willand 指出：“数据表明，人工智能带来的更高安全性和舒适度的前景可以激发购买决策。然而，尤其是欧洲受访者往往犹豫不决并对价格敏感。”</p><p>为人工智能功能付费的意愿也显示出同样明显的分歧。只有 23% 的欧洲司机表示愿意为人工智能功能付费，而中国司机的这一比例为 39%。研究表明，大多数用户现在期望人工智能功能成为标准配置，而不是可选的附加功能。 </p><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" width="851" height="1024" src="https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/in-vehicle-ai-improve-features-851x1024.jpg" alt="图表显示了车载人工智能可以显着改善公众视野中的哪些功能。" class="wp-image-16443" srcset="https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/in-vehicle-ai-improve-features-851x1024.jpg 851w, https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/in-vehicle-ai-improve-features-249x300.jpg 249w, https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/in-vehicle-ai-improve-features-768x924.jpg 768w, https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/in-vehicle-ai-improve-features-1277x1536.jpg 1277w, https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/in-vehicle-ai-improve-features-1703x2048.jpg 1703w, https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/in-vehicle-ai-improve-features-166x200.jpg 166w, https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/in-vehicle-ai-improve-features-237x285.jpg 237w, https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/in-vehicle-ai-improve-features-208x250.jpg 208w, https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/in-vehicle-ai-improve-features-83x100.jpg 83w, https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/in-vehicle-ai-improve-features-50x60.jpg 50w, https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/in-vehicle-ai-improve-features.jpg 1821w" sizes="(max-width: 851px) 100vw, 851px" /></figure><p> MHP 联席合伙人兼研究合著者 Nils Schaupensteiner 博士表示：“汽车公司需要创造具有明显附加值的创新，并开发其人工智能产品的直接和间接货币化，例如通过基于数据的商业模式和改进的服务”。</p><h3 class="wp-block-heading">车载人工智能机会</h3><p>尽管面临这些挑战，传统汽车制造商仍相对于科技巨头保持着信任优势。研究显示，64% 的客户信任已实施人工智能的汽车制造商，而苹果、谷歌和微软等科技公司的这一比例为 50%。 </p><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="1024" height="746" src="https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/in-vehicle-ai-stakeholders-trust-1024x746.jpg" alt="该图强调了公众对各利益相关者对车载人工智能的信任。" class="wp-image-16439" srcset="https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/in-vehicle-ai-stakeholders-trust-1024x746.jpg 1024w, https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/in-vehicle-ai-stakeholders-trust-300x219.jpg 300w, https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/in-vehicle-ai-stakeholders-trust-768x560.jpg 768w, https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/in-vehicle-ai-stakeholders-trust-1536x1119.jpg 1536w, https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/in-vehicle-ai-stakeholders-trust-274x200.jpg 274w, https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/in-vehicle-ai-stakeholders-trust-380x277.jpg 380w, https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/in-vehicle-ai-stakeholders-trust-343x250.jpg 343w, https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/in-vehicle-ai-stakeholders-trust-100x73.jpg 100w, https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/in-vehicle-ai-stakeholders-trust-60x44.jpg 60w, https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/in-vehicle-ai-stakeholders-trust.jpg 1821w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure><p>该研究确定了人工智能可以在整个汽车行业价值链中提供重要价值的几个关键领域，包括质量管理的模式识别、增强的数据管理能力、人工智能驱动的决策系统以及通过人工智能驱动的通信工具改善客户服务。</p><p> “原始设备制造商和供应商值得考虑新技术在整个价值链中提供的机会，”高级经理兼研究合著者 Augustin Friedel 解释道。 “然而，可能的用途多种多样，而且实施起来相当复杂。”</p><p>研究显示，<a href="https://iottechnews.com/news/nearly-80-percent-us-motorists-ai-voice-assistants/">虽然高达 79%</a>的受访者对驾驶员辅助系统、智能路线规划和预测性维护等人工智能功能感兴趣，但制造商在将这些功能货币化方面面临着重大挑战，尤其是在欧洲市场。 </p><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="687" height="1024" src="https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/interest-in-in-vehicle-ai-functions-687x1024.jpg" alt="该图显示了公众对各种车载人工智能功能的兴趣。" class="wp-image-16441" srcset="https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/interest-in-in-vehicle-ai-functions-687x1024.jpg 687w, https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/interest-in-in-vehicle-ai-functions-201x300.jpg 201w, https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/interest-in-in-vehicle-ai-functions-768x1145.jpg 768w, https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/interest-in-in-vehicle-ai-functions-1030x1536.jpg 1030w, https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/interest-in-in-vehicle-ai-functions-1374x2048.jpg 1374w, https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/interest-in-in-vehicle-ai-functions-134x200.jpg 134w, https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/interest-in-in-vehicle-ai-functions-191x285.jpg 191w, https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/interest-in-in-vehicle-ai-functions-168x250.jpg 168w, https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/interest-in-in-vehicle-ai-functions-67x100.jpg 67w, https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/interest-in-in-vehicle-ai-functions-40x60.jpg 40w, https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/interest-in-in-vehicle-ai-functions-scaled.jpg 1717w" sizes="(max-width: 687px) 100vw, 687px" /></figure><p><strong>另请参阅：</strong> <a href="https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/news/mit-breakthrough-could-transform-robot-training/"><strong>麻省理工学院的突破可能会改变机器人训练</strong></a></p><figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><a href="https://www.ai-expo.net/"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="728" height="90" src="https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/ai-expo-world-728x-90-01.png" alt="" class="wp-image-11874" srcset="https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/ai-expo-world-728x-90-01.png 728w, https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/ai-expo-world-728x-90-01-300x37.png 300w, https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/ai-expo-world-728x-90-01-380x47.png 380w, https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/ai-expo-world-728x-90-01-350x43.png 350w, https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/ai-expo-world-728x-90-01-100x12.png 100w, https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/ai-expo-world-728x-90-01-60x7.png 60w" sizes="(max-width: 728px) 100vw, 728px" /></a></figure><p><strong>想向行业领导者了解更多关于人工智能和大数据的知识吗？</strong>查看在阿姆斯特丹、加利福尼亚州和伦敦举办的<a href="https://www.ai-expo.net/">人工智能与大数据博览会</a>。该综合活动与其他领先活动同期举行，包括<a href="https://intelligentautomation-conference.com/northamerica/">智能自动化大会</a>、 <a href="https://www.blockchain-expo.com/">BlockX</a> 、<a href="https://digitaltransformation-week.com/">数字化转型周</a>以及<a href="https://www.cybersecuritycloudexpo.com/">网络安全与云博览会</a>。</p><p><a href="https://techforge.pub/events/">在此</a>探索由 TechForge 提供支持的其他即将举行的企业技术活动和网络研讨会。</p><p>后<a href="https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/news/western-drivers-remain-sceptical-in-vehicle-ai/